    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by Gunnar Henderson (83.29) as our primary anchor. Henderson\u2019s matchup against Shane Smith is quintessential for our 5x5 objectives; he benefits from a favorable platoon split, a wind-aided environment, and critically, a slow-delivery pitcher that boosts his SB upside\u2014the most scarce commodity in our build. Josh Lowe (72.20) and Nasim Nunez (69.88) provide the necessary supplemental speed and offensive floor, with Lowe capitalizing on a plus-matchup against a weak Reynaldo L\u00f3pez (6.36 xERA). These starts are essential, as the team prioritizes efficient, high-upside opportunities to maximize our game-cap usage.\n\nThe decision to bench Vladimir Guerrero Jr. (52.89) was the most difficult pivot of the morning. While his raw metrics remain elite, the optimizer favored players like Marcell Ozuna (55.23) and Jackson Merrill (54.95) due to their specific matchup dynamics\u2014Ozuna\u2019s documented BvP success and Merrill\u2019s wind-assisted matchup against Paul Skenes narrowly edged out Vlad Jr.\u2019s challenging encounter with Yoshinobu Yamamoto. We remain cautious of the \"Lineup Pending\" status across the board; should any of our projected order slots shift downward, particularly for lower-order hitters like Nunez or Lowe, we will monitor the score impact closely. With several high-skill arms like Skenes and Gausman on the mound today, our bench remains primed to cycle if official lineups reveal unfavorable shifts.",
